<HEAD>Deficiency of Vitamin Main Cause Of Blindness In Nepal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Each day, a child under the age of five
goes blind in Nepal because of a deficiency of vitamin A, a doctor
said Sunday.
   Chet Traj Pant, an opthalmologist, urged families to include
foods high in vitamin A in their diets. He said the foods include
green vegetables, fruits, carrots, fish and meat.
