<HEAD>Car Bomb Damages Police Station</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORENSE, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car bomb exploded near a police station in
this northwestern city early Sunday, slightly damaging the station
and six cars but causing no injuries, police said.
   The explosion occurred at 6:28 a.m.
   No one immediately claimed responsibility for the incident,
police said.
   Police believe the explosion was the work of the separatist
Guerrilla Army of the Galician People because the explosives used
were similar to those in past incidents attributed to the same group.
   The group is fighting for independence from Spain for the
four-province Galicia region.
   It has carried out a dozen attacks on electric plants, bank
offices, police cars and industries in the region in the past eight
months, police said.
