<HEAD>Bus-Train Crash Kills 11 In Zimbabwe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus was struck by a train at a railroad
crossing near Harare, killing 11 people and injuring 56, police said
Sunday.
   A police spokesman said nine bus passengers were killed instantly
and two died later at a hospital. All but one of the 56 people
injured were aboard the bus. Nine of the injured were hurt
seriously, he said.
